<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb861148f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s5381"><num value="5381">§ 5381.</num><heading> Definitions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purpose of this subchapter, “agency”, “Senior Executive Service position”, “career appointee”, and “senior executive” have the meanings set forth in <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s3132/a">section 3132(a) of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb8611490-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/95/454/tIV/s407/a">Pub. L. 95–454, title IV, § 407(a)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-13">Oct. 13, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1171">92 Stat. 1171</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/101/136/tVI/s625/b">Pub. L. 101–136, title VI, § 625(b)</ref>, <date date="1989-11-03">Nov. 3, 1989</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/103/823">103 Stat. 823</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb8611491-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb8611492-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idb8611493-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1989—<ref href="/us/pl/101/136">Pub. L. 101–136</ref> inserted “ ‘career appointee’,” before “and”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb8611494-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb8611495-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective 9 months after <date date="1978-10-13">Oct. 13, 1978</date>, and congressional review of provisions of sections 401 through 412 of <ref href="/us/pl/95/454">Pub. L. 95–454</ref>, see section 415(a)(1), (b) of <ref href="/us/pl/95/454">Pub. L. 95–454</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s3131">section 3131 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
